00:43:18.120 --> 00:43:23.060
Shin-ya Narusawa. He wants to be the Carl
Sagan of Japan. And as you can see, he's got

00:43:23.060 --> 00:43:30.080
already people, a lot of media there. There
were 23 observatories. Over two days, they

00:43:30.080 --> 00:43:35.210
were all looking at one star system that had
been recommended by Carl Sagan and Paul Horowitz,

00:43:35.210 --> 00:43:42.550
two of the icons of, of this whole world.
They looked. They didn't find anything but

00:43:42.550 --> 00:43:49.170
the whole idea was to figure out a way to
do everything together. I will end with this

00:43:49.170 --> 00:43:56.980
note. When I, after this was over and after
the stories began coming out about what they

00:43:56.980 --> 00:44:02.860
had been doing, I was with Shin-ya and he
started to get calls, a lot of calls and he

00:44:02.860 --> 00:44:08.760
was rolling his eyes and talking at length
and you could tell he was trying to calm people

00:44:08.760 --> 00:44:14.370
down. And he's speaking Japanese; I didn't
know what he was saying. But I later asked

00:44:14.370 --> 00:44:18.220
what was happening and he said, 'Well you
know whenever we do something like this and

00:44:18.220 --> 00:44:23.950
whenever we, there's, there's press about
it, we get all these calls from people saying,

00:44:23.950 --> 00:44:31.190
"Don't let them know we're here". [laughs]
"That this is dangerous". Now of course, we're

00:44:31.190 --> 00:44:38.360
not letting them know we're here. They're
just listening. But there is this whole discussion

00:44:38.360 --> 00:44:45.750
going on now about whether or not we should
also do METI which is 'messaging of extraterrestrial

00:44:45.750 --> 00:44:52.850
intelligence' which for the most part is not
being done because of calls like this. And

00:44:52.850 --> 00:44:58.470
Stephen Hawking very famously said the same
recently, that sending out messages would

00:44:58.470 --> 00:45:05.870
be too dangerous. That when superior technologies,
or societies with superior technology interact

00:45:05.870 --> 00:45:11.990
with those with inferior technology, meaning
us, that it always turns out poorly for the

00:45:11.990 --> 00:45:19.780
latter. And so, but that's a discussion that
really, that's going on now and it'll be exciting

00:45:19.780 --> 00:45:25.220
to, to follow. And a final thought, I kind
of bring this back to the world of belief.

00:45:25.220 --> 00:45:32.480
I mean there is this incredible body of science
now that's been put together. And yet we're

00:45:32.480 --> 00:45:38.360
now still left with this question of 'Well,
you know, extraterrestrial life. Is it bad?

00:45:38.360 --> 00:45:43.100
Is it good? Are they going to hurt us? Are
they going to not hurt us?' And, and in a

00:45:43.100 --> 00:45:50.560
way, it's sobering that that is still there
but it's the same process hopefully will occur

00:45:50.560 --> 00:45:57.770
where belief is gradually kind of chopped
down and knocked in, and put aside as science

00:45:57.770 --> 00:46:07.000
moves forward and finds realities which has
happened and hopefully will happen a lot more.

00:46:07.000 --> 00:46:09.220
Thank you.
[applause]

